SIMPLE: orderly
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orderly
<hw>Or"der*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Conformed to order;
in order; regular; <as>as, an <ex>orderly</ex> course or
plan</as>.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Observant of order, authority, or rule; hence,
obedient; quiet; peaceable; not unruly; <as>as, <ex>orderly</ex>
children; an <ex>orderly</ex> community.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Performed in good or established order;
well-regulated.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>orderly</xex> . . . march.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Clarendon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Being on duty; keeping order; conveying
orders.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Aids-de-camp and <xex>orderly</xex> men.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Orderly book</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a book for
every company, in which the general and regimental orders are
recorded.</cd> -- <col><b>Orderly officer</b></col>, <cd>the officer of
the day, or that officer of a corps or regiment whose turn it is to
supervise for the day the arrangements for food, cleanliness, etc.</cd>
<au>Farrow.</au> -- <col><b>Orderly room</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>The
court of the commanding officer, where charges against the men of the
regiment are tried.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>The office of the commanding
officer, usually in the barracks, whence orders emanate.</cd>
<au>Farrow.</au> -- <col><b>Orderly sergeant</b></col>, <cd>the first
sergeant of a company.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orderly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Orderly
<hw>Or"der*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>According to due
order; regularly; methodically; duly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are blunt; go to it <qex>orderly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orderly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Orderly
<hw>Or"der*ly</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Orderlies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>A noncommissioned officer or soldier who attends a superior officer
to carry his orders, or to render other service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Orderlies</qex> were appointed to watch the palace.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A street sweeper.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Mayhew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ordinability</ent>⟦br⟧
